%N A392884 a(n) is the minimum total surface area of four-element sets of distinct integer-sided cuboids that fill an n X n X n cube.
%C A392884 Total surface area of four-element sets of cuboids is given by the sum of surface area 2*(x*y+y*z+z*x) of each cuboid x X y X z in the set.
%C A392884 Proof of the formula: the total surface area equals 6*n^2 + 2*I, where I is the total area of internal interfaces. The partition {(n-1) X n X n, 1 X (n-1) X n, 1 X 1 X (n-1), 1 X 1 X 1} attains I = n^2 + n + 1. Conversely, every dissection of a box into at most 4 boxes has a fault plane (a plane meeting the interior of the box crossed by no piece); applying this recursively, I >= n^2 + n + 1. The optimal partitions are exactly {(n-1) X n X n, 1 X (n-1) X n, 1 X 1 X j, 1 X 1 X (n-j)} with j != n-j, up to symmetry. - _Diego Lago Gómez_, Jul 04 2026
%H A392884 Michael De Vlieger, <a href="/A392884/b392884.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 3..10000</a>
%H A392884 Diego Lago Gómez, <a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2607.15894">The minimum surface area of k unequal boxes tiling a cube: sharp thresholds, a fault-free law, and a reduction to two dimensions</a>, arXiv:2607.15894 [math.CO], 2026. See p. 2.
%H A392884 <a href="/index/Rec#order_03">Index entries for linear recurrences with constant coefficients</a>, signature (3,-3,1).
%F A392884 From _Diego Lago Gómez_, Jul 04 2026: (Start)
%F A392884 a(n) = 8*n^2 + 2*n + 2.
%F A392884 a(n) = 3*a(n-1) - 3*a(n-2) + a(n-3) for n >= 6.
%F A392884 G.f.: x^3*(80 - 102*x + 38*x^2)/(1 - x)^3.
%F A392884 a(n) = A033585(n) + 2. (End)
%F A392884 E.g.f.: 2*exp(x)*(1 + 5*x + 4*x^2) - 2 - 12*x - 19*x^2. - _Stefano Spezia_, Jul 11 2026
%e A392884 According to A384311(3) there are four sets of cuboids in total that fill 3 X 3 X 3 cube:
%e A392884  {(3 X 3 X 2), (3 X 2 X 1), (2 X 1 X 1), (1 X 1 X 1)} with total area = 80,
%e A392884  {(3 X 3 X 2), (3 X 1 X 1), (2 X 2 X 1), (2 X 1 X 1)} with total area = 82,
%e A392884  {(3 X 3 X 1), (3 X 2 X 2), (2 X 2 X 1), (2 X 1 X 1)} with total area = 88,
%e A392884  {(3 X 3 X 1), (3 X 2 X 1), (2 X 2 X 2), (2 X 2 X 1)} with total area = 92.
%e A392884 Therefore a(3) = 80 since the minimum total surface area of the four cuboids is 80.
%t A392884 CoefficientList[Series[x^3*(80 - 102*x + 38*x^2)/(1 - x)^3, {x, 0, 45}], x][[4 ;; -1]] (* _Michael De Vlieger_, Jul 23 2026 *)
